product.title: Osaka Japanese Street Stalls Building Sets
product.body_html:
• Description
  • FAQ
  • Shipping

  • Experience the life of running your Own Favorite Japanese Street Stalls

    Japan pride themselves for their yummy food and fascinating decoration from their famous street stalls. Now you have the opportunity to experience the life of a Japanese Street Market Stall manager. We have picked 8 cute Japanese street stalls for you to build, role play, and learn how to run a Japanese street stall in your own comfort room. The perfect gift for your loved ones!

    🌸 Compatible with leading blocks of standard size (16mm)
    🌸 Each set has over 60 pieces and varies with different sets
    🌸 Each set includes mini dolls
    🌸 Excludes original box to protect the environment. For further details please see below.*


    Our first cute Japanese Street Stall is Takoyaki たこ焼き or "octopus balls"  蛸焼 is a ball-shaped Japanese snack or appetizer made of a wheat flour-based batter and cooked in a special molded pan. It is typically filled with minced or diced octopus, tempura scraps, pickled ginger, and green onion. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 64 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.6 x 5.0 x 6.8cm



    Our second cute Japanese Street Stall is Soft cream is a Japanized word for soft-serve ice cream made from natural favours. A must dessert to have when you go to Japan to fulfil your hungry tummy. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 71 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 7.0cm



    Our third cute Japanese Street Stall is Tempura. Tempura is a typical Japanese dish usually consisting of seafood, meat, and vegetables that have been battered and deep-fried. A must-try food when you are over in Japan. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 66 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 7.3 cm


    Our forth cute Japanese Street Stall is Yaki-zakana selling their popular delicious grilled or fried fish. It is one of the essential dishes in Japanese cuisine today. Yakizakana is a far more common dish than sushi in the lives of most people in Japan. It’s an extremely popular breakfast food and also makes regular appearances at lunch and dinner. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 71 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 7.9cm



    Our fifth cute Japanese Street Stall is Wagasa 和傘, made from oil-paper umbrellas. It is a great accessory for a photoshoot when you are over in Japan, wearing your beautiful Kimono. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 76 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 7.8 cm


    Our sixth cute Japanese Street facility is a telephone booth. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 43 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 6.8cm


    Our seventh cute Japanese Street Stall is Sushi, selling their popular delicious Sushi and seafood. Sushi comes from a Japanese word meaning "sour rice," and it's the rice that's at the heart of sushi. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 85 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.2 x 7.1cm



    Our final cute Japanese Street Stall is Kimono きもの / 着物. It is a symbol of longevity and good fortune. The word "kimono", which actually means a "thing to wear". Traditional Japanese kimono is more formal than yukata but can still be worn for both casual and formal occasions. Traditional kimono have gorgeous designs and coloring and can be worn or used for ornamental decoration. With the exquisite details as shown. It contains 69 pieces. Dimensions measure 6.4 x 4.8 x 6.6 cm

    Buy the complete set of 8 stalls to complete your Japanese street at a discounted price! 

    Our building blocks are designed with advanced engineering features providing a unique building experience for all building block fans. We've created an easy-to-follow instruction booklet for each set so you can build your new Japanese town hassle-free.

    The perfect gift for those who love their crafts!

    You will love seeing your family and friends in excitement when they receive our building blocks, leaving an everlasting smile on your loved ones by surprising them with these super innovative and cool building blocks today.

    * Our Building Block sets are packaged in safe and secured protective bags. They do NOT come in the original box to reduce the carbon footprint, save the planet and reduce postage cost on your behalf. It will come with all the pieces and a detailed instruction booklet for you to follow along. 

    Standard Blocks: These blocks are compatible with other famous brands.

    Features

    🌸 100% premium quality (ABS) plastic
    🌸 Sharp brilliant colors and solid feel
    🌸 Challenging and rewarding to stimulate all brains
    🌸 High-quality durable non-toxic green material

    WARNING: CHOKING HAZARD - Contain small parts; not suitable for children under 6 years old unless there is adult supervision.


  • Where do we ship worldwide? Yes, we ship to over 300 countries and proud to provide free shipping to the United States, the United Kingdom, Australia, New Zealand, and many countries in Europe.

    What are the blocks made from?     All our building blocks are manufactured from a High-Quality Premium strong, resilient plastic known as acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS) and will stand the test of time and provide hours of fun building their own creations

    Does this help with stress and development?     Our building blocks are a great way to relieve stress and engage in meaningful and joyful conversations. As children comment on their building creations, they develop important communication skills including the ability to explain ideas, describe their work, talk about the process and verbalize challenges that they had along the way. 

    Are these compatible with other leading brands? Yes, these are traditional/standard-sized blocks so they are compatible with other leading brands.

    CHOKING HAZARD: Small parts. Not for children under 6 years old

     

  • We are proud to offer FREE tracked shipping to over 300 countries worldwide including the United States, Canada, United Kingdom, Australia, New Zealand, Germany, France, Italy, Austria, Netherlands, and many others. If you are wondering if we ship to your country please head over to our Shipping Policy.

    Packaging time: 1-3 Business days

    Shipping time: Est 5-30 Business days
